dismissalComment.html: Done in the flight. Tharanga went down the track but couldn't get to the pitch of the ball and ended up slicing it towards long-off. Coventry rushed in from the deep and lunged forward to take a good catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Another celebration .. this time like Brazilian footballer Bebeto ... It was the full delivery, almost a yorker, which has taken out the middle stump. The batsman was looking for the big hit. Mpofu does a movement like Bebeto - as if he is cradling a child

Now Price and Mpofu do some stylish celebrations! It was a full delivery which has been square driven straight to point! Even as Mpofu cradles an imaginary baby, Taibu, who has just had a second child, envelops him with a hug. And Price joins in and he and Mpofu have a little dance - tapping each others' foot.

dismissalText.commentary: Dilhara Fernando run out (â€ Taibu) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Taibu you beauty! It was nudged to say squarish short leg ... Fernando stepped down the track for a single and was sent back. He hadn't gone down too long but Taibu was very quick. Very alert. He dashed off, picked the ball, had already removed his right glove, and under-armed a direct hit!

commentPreTextItems.html: BO J: "makes me wish I was back in Harare watching the match!  I've been
really impressed with how quickly the Zimbabwe team is growing and improving as weget more and more match experience against better sides.  Well done guys!!  Let's keep it going for the final"

commentTextItems.html: Sizzling! Full delivery outside off and Taylor crashes it to the cover boundary. Zimbabwe win by 8 wickets.

commentPostTextItems.html: What stood out not only in this game but in all their wins so far in this tournament is how calm, collected, clinical, professional and in control they have been. The chases have been all done without any hiccups. Like a team that knows how to win.
Bonyongo: "Best of all - I think we can now stop using the term "shock win" when Zim wins a game....we're a decent team, and we can win games just like anybody else...fantastic!"

Nelson Maqandisa: "After this encouraging display by Zimbabwe, i hope the authorities will give us a half working day on Wednesday to watch the final like they did when Zimbabwe played Brazil in an international friendly soccer match."
Allen Robinson: "Call me a fair weather supporter but if Zim continue to play like this I will definitely be coming back to watch."

Dave: "This has been a clinical show up by Zim, just hope and prays that they can keep the consistency going into the final! None the less, good, spirited all round performance!  Mugabe can be proud. "
Bryan Morton: "For those of us who have continued to support Zim through the hard times - *this* is the payback.  Hugely proud of the guys for the way they've performed this series."

Don't know whether this is true but here is Kangon: "Actually Sri Lanka hate playing against Zimbabwe on 7th of the month, I guess.They've lost against Zim in 7th Nov 1998, 7th April 2003 and today, 7th Jun 2010."
Please to hang on for the quotes from the post-match ceremony.

Dilshan "They bowled well in the middle overs. When the ball got old. We were short of 30 runs. As I said in the morning, 260 would have been a good score to defend. Our bowlers did well. Main two bowlers didn't play today; they will come back for the final. Angelo also might be fit and make our middle order stronger. We can learn from this game for the final.:

Chigumbura: "Very happy. Fantastic performance from the batsmen, especially BT. We struggled with the new ball seamers but the spinners have bowled really well all through this season. We seamers have to work hard. If I lose the toss on the final, it's just the matter of doing well on field. Taylor is a fantastic player; I hope he does well in the final also."

Man of the Match is Brendan Taylor : "The pitch was slightly slow than the first game here against India. But it still played ok. We felt that they should have got more. So we just concentrated on getting a foundation for the batsmen coming in. I am trying to find some consistency with my batting and it's a nice feeling to get a few good scores here. Really pleasing with the wins. I try to tell myself that stay relaxed as much as possible; you have a job to do and go out there and do it. They [Sri Lanka] have rested some players in this game and so definitely the contest will be stiffer in the final."
That's it from us. Good bye and good luck

commentTextItems.html: low full toss on the off stump line, pushed to mid-off for a single
Another wide down the leg side. He was trying the slower one but the release went awry
the slow bouncer around off, swatted behind square-leg
good yorker on the middle and Taylor stabs it back down the track
Wide outside the leg stump. Just four more now

commentPreTextItems.html: Sandeep: "Taylor has been playing tournament of his life....With 3 man of the matches  so far , he would be on his way to make a record for most number of man of the match in a tournament."
Faiz: "Now Taylor overtook Rohit Sharma as the highest scorer in this tournament. Well played"

commentTextItems.html: Thwack! Full pitched on the leg and middle and Taibu whips it to deep midwicket for three runs
fullish, just outside off, driven hard but straight to deep cover

commentTextItems.html: Fernando responds with a yorker, dug out towards third man. Just nine more now
Stunner! Fabulicious! What a hit. It was a full delivery around off and he punched it over long-off. Classy. Stylish. Superb timing.
short in length, on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
taps this to square-leg and they cross over
goes for the yorker, dug out towards mid-on for a quick single
leans forward to nurdle it past square-leg

stretches forward to turn it to short midwicket. Just a single so far
leans forward to work it behind square-leg
spins in from outside off, pushed down the track
tossed full outside off, driven to mid-off
The slow bouncer.. Taylor was in two minds.. tries to pull but by then the ball had sailed over

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan st â€ Taibu b Utseya 78 (66b 9x4 2x6 84m) SR: 118.18

dismissalComment.html: Stumped! Done in by the floater. Dilshan was down the track for the big shot but the ball drifted away and he ended up chasing it well away from his body and missed. Taibu did the rest

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c Masakadza b Utseya 6 (13b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 46.15

dismissalComment.html: Utseya takes his second wicket. He floated it outside off and got it to straighten as well. Chandimal, who had cut a similar delivery for couple of runs earlier, went for the cut shot again. But this time the ball flew straight to backward point. Utseya wins this mini-battle.

headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamara Kapugedera c & b Masakadza 12 (16b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: now that's a celebration. Soft dismissal, Kapu doesn't quite get to the pitch of a length ball and chips an easy return catch to Masakadza, who throws the ball in the air, and then lifts his shirt to show his vest with "just married" inscribed on it

headshotImage.caption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c Coventry b Cremer 69 (97b 5x4 0x6 138m) SR: 71.13

dismissalComment.html: Done in the flight. Tharanga went down the track but couldn't get to the pitch of the ball and ended up slicing it towards long-off. Coventry rushed in from the deep and lunged forward to take a good catch

dismissalText.commentary: Jeevan Mendis c Taylor b Cremer 7 (8b 1x4 0x6 10m) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: It was a pretty short delivery actually if not a long hop. Mendis opened his stance and went for the pull but got more elevation than distance. Taylor moved in from deep midwicket to collect that

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Thilan Samaraweera run out (Chigumbura/â€ Taibu) 16 (31b 1x4 0x6 46m) SR: 51.61

dismissalComment.html: Samaraweera is run out and he storms off Oh what a dreary mess. It was pushed past non-striker and the straight midwicket fielder moves to his left to cut it off and fumbles. Samaraweera thinks there is a single there and rushes down the track. Thirimanne turns, sees Samaraweera run in but stays put at his end. Both end up together. And the throw goes to Taibu. Gone!

headshotImage.caption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera b Mpofu 8 (16b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Another celebration .. this time like Brazilian footballer Bebeto ... It was the full delivery, almost a yorker, which has taken out the middle stump. The batsman was looking for the big hit. Mpofu does a movement like Bebeto - as if he is cradling a child

headshotImage.caption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne c Taylor b Mpofu 15 (21b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: Now Price and Mpofu do some stylish celebrations! It was a full delivery which has been square driven straight to point! Even as Mpofu cradles an imaginary baby, Taibu, who has just had a second child, envelops him with a hug. And Price joins in and he and Mpofu have a little dance - tapping each others' foot.

dismissalComment.html: And then they were one. Price slowed up the pace and also gave it bit of air outside off.. Thushara went for the slog sweep and ended up dragging it to  deep midwicket

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Dilhara Fernando run out (â€ Taibu) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Taibu you beauty! It was nudged to say squarish short leg ... Fernando stepped down the track for a single and was sent back. He hadn't gone down too long but Taibu was very quick. Very alert. He dashed off, picked the ball, had already removed his right glove, and under-armed a direct hit!

dismissalComment.html: Masakadza's new wife must have winced. A bouncer on the leg stump line and he goes for the pull but gloves it behind for a leg-side catch to the keeper.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor not out 119 (137b 9x4 1x6 188m) SR: 86.86
Chamu Chibhabha lbw b Dilshan 58 (81b 4x4 1x6 103m) SR: 71.6

dismissalComment.html: Plumb in front. It landed on a length and skidded on straight .. Chibhabha went back and tried to work it to the leg side but was beaten by the lack of turn. It went on straight and skidded quickly to catch him in front ...
